              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The radioactive beam facility in Louvain-la-Neuve."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "N",
                "subentry_number": null,
                "author": "T.DAVINSON+",
                "reference": {
                  "code": "J,NIM/A,454,350,2000",
                  "field": {
                    "reference_type": "J",
                    "reference": {
                      "code": "NIM/A",
                      "number": null,
                      "volume": "454",
                      "part": null,
                      "issue": null,
                      "page": "350"
                    },
                    "date": 2000
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Details of detector system."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Pure 12-C target (with a thickness of 105 mug/cm2) was",
                "used in the measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Outgoing charged particles were detected",
                "in three large-area silicon strip detectors 300 mum",
                "thick.   A total of 320 strip detectors were used, with",
                "only 5 of them not working properly.  The forward",
                "detector array (LEDA, Louvain-Edinburgh Detector Array)",
                "consisted of 8 sectors each containing 16 strips.",
                "The polar angles covered were 4 - 12 degree and an",
                "azimuthal range was from 0 upto 360 degrees.",
                "The detector arrays placed at larger angles (called",
                " LAMPs because  of  their  lampshade  geometry)  had  6",
                "sectors each and they were covering polar angles",
                "20 - 65 (LAMP1) and 115 - 160 degrees (LAMP2)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 18 MeV 6-He+ beam.  The only detected",
                "impurity in the beam were the heh+2 ions.  Events",
                "produced by this exotic impurity were easily recognized",
                "and removed in an off-line analysis."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Information on the mass of detected particles was",
                "obtained by the method, using the detector and",
                "cyclotron RF signals as start and stop pulses.  The",
                "final mass resolution in the LEDA detector was good",
                "enough to mainly separate alpha-particles from 6-He",
                "nuclei, while in the LAMP detectors the small distance",
                "to the target resulted in a poor mass separation.",
                "Therefore, to get a clear identification of outgoing",
                "particles in LAMPs, time-of-flight was combined with",
                "mass determination from kinematics of the coincidence",
                "events."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The total collected charge was monitored",
                "by Faraday cup."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "79-AU-197(2-HE-6,EL)79-AU-197,,DA",
